title: Firefox Bookmarks - Missing when Firefox not executing overnight
content:
I've been having this issue for several weeks now. I have an HP desktop PC, with Windows 11, and the latest update is:

2025-10 Cumulative Update for Windows 11, version 25H2 for x64-based Systems (KB5070773) (26200.6901) - which happen ed yesterday, and this problem has been going on for a week now.

When I click on Bookmarks -> Manage Bookmarks; all my Bookmark Folders/sub-folders are listed, however when you click on an individual folder/bookmark - the Bookmark Properties are totally blank at the bottom of the screen. The RED ARROWS point to the area where any bookmark listed all have the same missing Properties area.

Notice the icon to the left of any bookmark? It looks like a globe. All individual bookmarks have this same icon, where before they could have and did have different icons to the left.

The BOOKMARK NAME is displayed, but the URL ADDRESS is missing for each and every bookmark listed.

BIG PROBLEM: When I leave my PC on overnight with nothing executing, the next day when I launch Firefox, what was there before and functioning, now all bookmarks are missing as described above. Nothing changed overnight and Firefox changed something by itself that I didn't initiated.

Please investigate, correct the code, and send out an update immediately. IF NOT FIXED ASAP, AFTER USING FIREFOX SINCE IT WAS FIRST INTRODUCED - I AM GOING TO DUMP THIS BROWSER FOREVER. ARON COOK

title: Why browser caching sometimes shows old results for dynamic tools?
content:
I recently noticed a scenario where a web tool loads updated data (via JavaScript and backend API), but the browser (and proxy cache) still serves outdated content when viewed on a different device. Clearing the browser cache fixes it, but that’s not a scalable solution for users.

I’m curious: does Firefox’s caching behavior differ for pages that use heavy client-side updates (e.g., incremental score calculators) compared to standard static pages? Should we be explicitly sending cache-control headers like no-store or must-revalidate to prevent stale data?

Any documented guidance on how Firefox handles cache revalidation for dynamic web-apps would be helpful.

Thanks in advance for any pointers.

title: Spurious Error 403
content:
I am a pensioner in te UK. Due to restricted mobility I spend a lot of time using Firefox to access many web sites. This normally works perfectly. Today I tried to access the web site of national chain store specialising in outdoor clothing and equipment because I need a new showerproof jacket. I have never used that site before, yet Firefox reported Error 403 : Forbidden. Have you people never been told tat error messages are supposed to be useful? What is Forbidden. Why when it has not happemed before?

The web site is https://www.millets.co.uk/

I have a web site so I have other browsers just for checking for layout problems.

I tried Chromium, same error but the message said You are not authorised to access this site. Presumably that is what your incompetent message should have said. But why should a pensioner trying to buy something from a chain store ever need any sort of authorisation?

I tried Opera. Connected me no problem!

I tried Edge. Connected me no problem.

Clearly somebody somewhere is an incompetent idiot, but it isn't me. So who is it? If it is yourselves then please do something to fix this.

content:

title: Perdí todos mis marcadores aunque le di a Sync
content:
Estaba en mi sesión abierta con este mail, en win 10 y pasé a win 11. Descargué todo bien y cuando inicio sesión, por lo general (y en otras ocasiones) firefox solo empezaba a descargar todos mis marcadores anteriores y ya, o sino iba a una pagina donde me mostraba todo lo que tenia guardado, simplemente elegia el que quería y ya, incluso tenia de sesiones mucho mas viejas.

Ahora perdí todo?

title: Account limit reached for profile — deleted others but still blocked.
content: I am having trouble with signing in and syncing after making other profiles. I was under the impression that the profiles would be under one email and tried signing into two other accounts which worked but then I saw that my original profile was disconnected. When trying to re-sign in I kept getting a pop-up saying “account limit reached for this profile,” but the profile isn’t signed into anything. I signed out of the two extra profiles and deleted them. I signed out of my other devices that had the same email attached. I also went into my profile folder through “about:profiles” and deleted the 'signedInUser.json' file, cleared the cache, restarted Firefox, and even tried refreshing Firefox through the troubleshooting page. I also checked my Firefox account online and removed any connected devices before signing back in again. the only way i can sign in with the email is to create a new profile but that leaves my og- with all my bookmarks and extensions- without a way to sync.
creator: JasminJean769
